comments: The next term (a(9)) has 121 digits. - _Harvey P. Dale_, Nov 23 2013
formula: a(n) is asymptotic to c^F(2n) where F(n) is the n-th Fibonacci's number A000045(n) and c=1.1137378757136... - _Benoit Cloitre_, May 31 2005
maple: A003818 := proc(n) option remember; if n <= 2 then 1 else (A003818(n-1)^3+1)/A003818(n-2); fi; end;
